method proposed by J. Harms was used, nearly always involving a combined 
anterior and posterior surgical approach. At the Division of Orthopaedics of the 
Ospedale Maria Adelaide in Turin between 1993 and June 1995 a total of 16 
patients affected with vertebral metastases caused by neoplasms of different 
