interviewing the patients over the phone during August of 1995. In the cases at 
the Ist Division of Orthopaedics the number of levels that were instrumented 
were on the average 2.5, at follow-up 83% of the patients stated that they were 
satisfied, while only 7.4% were unsatisfied. In the second series (Ospedale 
Maria Adelaide) the number of levels instrumented was on the average 8, at 
follow-up 62.5% of the patients said that they were satisfied, while 31.8% said 
that they were unsatisfied.

